
== kernel / boot ==
[x] paging, heap allocator, selftests
[x] task scheduling, semaphores
[x] PCI, RTL8139, ARP, UDP, IP, DHCP
[x] FAT16 + ramdisk, unified VFS
[x] 9P/2000 server over UDP (port 9999)
[x] trilog (prolog) REPL - core.pl loads from VFS, FFI builtins for ls/tree/tick/sleep/path_join/net_init/dhcp
[ ] FAT16 file write (open/write)
[ ] ELF32 binary loading + exec
[ ] switch bootloader from --kernel to GRUB/limine
[ ] ring0 minimal kernel - exec elf32, recompile from tcc

== 9p / vfs ==
[x] 9P server serves unified VFS over UDP
[x] c9 client + SWI-Prolog treewalk working end-to-end (tools/c9/)
[ ] use 9P as the kernel-side VFS backend (interact with 9P not VFS directly)
[ ] kernel reaches out to 9P config server on boot (bootstrap/persistence)
[ ] FAT16 map exposed cleanly over 9P
[ ] DNS / outside 9P config server

== networking ==
[x] net_init/0 and dhcp/0 as non-blocking prolog FFI
[ ] thread ethernet packet handling
[ ] IP path inefficiency (works but suboptimal)
[ ] UDP sockets API

== prolog ==
[x] trilog embedded freestanding
[x] core.pl loaded from /fd/core.pl at REPL startup
[x] OS FFI: ls/2 file_size/2 tick/1 ksleep/1 path_join/3 tree/1 net_init/0 dhcp/0 help/0 listing/0
[ ] ip/1 — unify with current DHCP-assigned IP (or fail if not acquired)
[ ] system testing from prolog over 9P
[ ] reproducible test harness

== misc ==
